{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4e576c1-8392-49db-a23c-164fab1a662d","content":"**3. Create a GitHub environment**\n\nIn your repo settings → **Environments** → create one called `nuget`. This ties the OIDC token to a specific environment that NuGet.org verifies.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of steps:**\n\n| Where | Action |\n|-------|--------|\n| **NuGet.org** | Register trusted publisher (owner: `myorg`, repo: `mylib`, workflow: `publish.yml`, environment: `nuget`) |\n| **GitHub repo** | Create `nuget` environment in Settings → Environments |\n| **Workflow** | `.github/workflows/publish.yml` (created above) |\n\n**To publish:** push a tag like `git tag v1.0.0 && git push --tags`. The workflow uses OIDC — no API key needed. The `dotnet nuget push` command automatically picks up the OIDC token when `id-token: write` is set and the trusted publisher is configured on NuGet.org.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"38046536-4a6e-40b0-b5c9-174e55abe61f","outputTokens":226,"requestId":"A40F:30C63A:13F188B:165D44F:69F93EF9"},"id":"576ba915-bdc2-459f-923a-8f5f62d4f5aa","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:51:12.172Z","parentId":"e2a87078-bfd3-450d-98b6-1dee2560d3ea"}
